title.narrative: INTEGRATED SOCIAL PROGRAMME

description.narrative: Child focused equity-sensitive data and evidence generation, knowledge sharing and capacity building for more transparent and efficient allocation and expenditure of investments of social services for children, which contributes to Access To Inclusive Social Protection, Access To Inclusive Social Protection (Covid), Cross Sectoral - Children With Disabilities, Cross Sectoral - Gender Discriminatory Roles And Practices, Evaluation, Operations Support To Programme Delivery, Promotion Of Care, Mental Health And Psychosocial Well-Being And Justice, Reducing Child Poverty, Reducing Child Poverty (Covid), Research. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Communications, Advocacy And Public Engagement, Community Engagement, Social And Behaviour Change, Data, Research, Evaluation And Knowledge Management, Evaluations, Research And Data, Operational Support To Programme Delivery, Risk-Informed Humanitarian And Development Nexus Programming, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, Systems Strengthening To Leave No One Behind. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: Improved policy environment, budgets and systems for all children, especially the most excluded, guided by improved knowledge and disaggregated data

description.narrative: Due to non-engagement principles from February 2021, UNICEF put on hold technical and capacity building support to government partners on social protection. Throughout the year, UNICEF facilitated the much-needed social protection sector coordination among development partners and directly implemented the Humanitarian Child Grant Programme for 5,300 vulnerable households to meet the humanitarian needs of vulnerable children and families due to lack of government’s social protection programme in peri-urban township of Yangon. | Status:Constrained | As-of Date:14/01/2022
